## 1) Change the font size inside each testimonial card

You already have a dedicated CSS variable controlling *all* testimonial typography:

```css
:root { --testimonial-scale: 0.5; } /* 1.10 for +10%, 0.90 for -10% */
```

…and that variable is used to scale the three text pieces (`.t-name`, `.t-tagline`, `.t-quote`) via `clamp(...) * var(--testimonial-scale)` later in the same file. fileciteturn0file1

**What to do**

- **Global change (affects every page):** raise this in `assets/css/corporate-1.9.5.css` (put near the end or adjust the existing declaration):

```css
:root {
  --testimonial-scale: 1;   /* 1 = 100% (baseline), 1.1 = +10%, 0.9 = -10% */
}
```

- **Only in the testimonials section:** set the variable on the section container in your CSS:

```css
#testimonials { --testimonial-scale: 1.1; } /* +10% in this section only */
```

Because the fonts are defined with `clamp()` and then multiplied by `--testimonial-scale`, everything scales proportionally and remains responsive. See `.t-name`, `.t-tagline`, and `.t-quote` definitions in your CSS. fileciteturn0file1  
The testimonials section itself is the element with `id="testimonials"` in your HTML. fileciteturn0file2

