## B) Make the “Testimonials” title and the ‹ / › buttons smaller on very narrow screens (< 400 px)

You already scale the nav buttons down at ≤420 px; add one more narrower breakpoint for ≤400 px and tighten the title size. The title element is `.t-title` inside the testimonials header in your HTML. fileciteturn0file2

**Add this directly below your existing `@media (max-width: 420px)` block, at the end of `corporate-1.9.5.css`:**
```css
/* === PATCH: Extra‑small phones (≤400px) — tighter title + smaller arrow discs === */
@media (max-width: 400px) {
  .section--testimonials .t-title {
    /* reduce from clamp(2.2rem, 2rem + 1.2vw, 3.2rem) */
    font-size: clamp(1.45rem, 6vw, 1.9rem);
  }

  /* keep tap target ≥44px for usability while shrinking the glyph */
  .section--testimonials .t-btn {
    inline-size: 44px;
    block-size: 44px;
    font-size: 24px; /* chevron size */
  }
}
```
Your existing ≤420 px rule currently sets the buttons to 48 px; this ≤400 px rule will override it when space is tighter. fileciteturn0file1

